<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-05T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-05T08:00:00-05:00" n="295" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d295">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 851.857Su8/36</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-05T13:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1916, 1 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>4101. Your 3141, April 4, 4 [7] p. m., and 3144,<note n="1" xml:id="d295fn1">Not printed.</note> April 4, 8 p. m.</p>
                            <p>British Admiralty inform me after consulting their records that <hi rend="italic">Sussex</hi> was never used as a transport or
                                troopship, and state further that route followed by <hi rend="italic">Sussex</hi> on her last trip is not the one
                                followed by transports or troopships proceeding from England.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>